&lt;p&gt;The Sales Operations Specialist supports the effectiveness of the sales organization by coordinating enablement programs, improving operational processes, maintaining key sales data, and helping execute strategic sales initiatives.&amp;nbsp;As a Sales Operations Specialist, you will play a critical role in enabling the success of our sales organization. You are proactive, communicative, resourceful, and detail-oriented. Equally important, you exercise strong judgment—knowing when to lead, when to collaborate, and when to provide seamless support behind the scenes to help the team operate at its best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: This is a hybrid role and requires working from our Denver office at least two days per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✨ What You’ll Do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training &amp;amp; Communications: &lt;/strong&gt;Coordinate onboarding and ongoing sales enablement programs; create and maintain training materials; and manage internal sales communications across written, recorded, and live formats. Partner with subject matter experts to ensure content is accurate, relevant, and up to date.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Analysis &amp;amp; Improvement: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Analyze sales processes and operational metrics to identify opportunities for greater efficiency and consistency. Help document and improve sales processes to standardize workflows and make day-to-day work more repeatable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain sales data quality, prepare recurring reports and dashboards, support Salesforce data hygiene, and assist with forecasting or pipeline reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;: Support key initiatives by coordinating activities, tracking deliverables, communicating progress, and following up on action items to help ensure projects are completed accurately and on schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎯 What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in Sales Operations, Sales Enablement, Revenue Operations, Marketing Operations, and/or a similar role within a sales-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with exceptional attention to detail and the ability to manage competing priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong computer skills, including proficiency with spreadsheets, presentation development, and professional business communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and self-motivated, with strong prioritization, multitasking, and time management skills. Process-oriented and adaptable to evolving business needs and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce preferred; experience with any CRM platform is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative team player with a commitment to delivering high-quality work and supporting the success of the broader organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with a sense of urgency and effectively manage multiple deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Due to export-control regulations, we can only consider “US persons” for this role. A “US person” is defined by federal law as a US citizen, lawful permanent resident (green card holder), refugee, or asylee. We are not able to provide visa sponsorship or transfer.*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
